Crucible OS is a Linux distro build (live-build + Calamares config) plus a
set of setup/mode-switching scripts. It does not vendor, fork, or modify any
of the upstream projects it installs or builds on — they are pulled in as
ordinary packages/repos and configured via the files in modes/, drivers/,
and iso/.

- Ubuntu — base distribution. https://ubuntu.com — Canonical Ltd.
- live-build (Debian Live Systems Project) — ISO build tooling.
  https://salsa.debian.org/live-team/live-build
- Calamares — installer framework. https://calamares.io
- Crucible12 — the local AI stack modes/ai/ is ported from.
  https://github.com/Mr-Pythoneer/Crucible12 (MIT) — see its own NOTICE for
  the further upstream projects it depends on (OpenCode, llama.cpp, Qwen3,
  Unsloth GGUF quantizations).
- Proton-GE, Wine (WineHQ), Bottles, GameMode, MangoHud, Lutris, Steam —
  installed by modes/gaming/setup/*.sh, each under its own license.
- FreeCAD, Blender, Kdenlive, DaVinci Resolve, ffmpeg / BtbN's FFmpeg-Builds —
  installed by modes/creative/setup/*.sh, each under its own license.
- WhiteSur GTK/icon/shell themes (vinceliuice) — installed by
  modes/normal/setup/01-install-whitesur-theme.sh, MIT License.

Crucible OS's own scripts, configs, and documentation are MIT-licensed — see
LICENSE.
